---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Free-Shipping Promotions in 2026';
const description = 'A practical guide to Shopify email apps for free-shipping promotions, covering eligibility, margin, cart recovery, pricing context, source links, and tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Behavioral free-shipping eligibility and suppression','Granular events, segments, and conditional flows','Offer governance and margin analysis are essential','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail free-shipping campaigns via email and SMS','Accessible promotion automation','Incentive frequency can become expensive','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Lean stores with one clear shipping offer','Focused campaign sequences','Less advanced offer analytics should be checked','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Drip','DTC stores measuring offer impact on repeat orders','Commerce automation and reporting','May exceed a small store’s needs','https://www.drip.com/features'],['Shopify Email','Simple native promotion announcements','Fast product and audience setup','Limited eligibility branching','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Free shipping can remove a purchase barrier, but it also changes margin and behavior. The right email app helps a store decide who needs the offer, what order threshold applies, and when the offer should stop.</p><p>We prioritize eligibility, threshold logic, purchase suppression, and margin-aware testing. Verify current pricing, coupon behavior, and shipping rules from official sources before publishing a promotion.</p><h2>Shortlist for free-shipping offers</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First test</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Threshold-based segment':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Campaign promotion':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Cart-to-offer sequence':a[0]==='Drip'?'Offer cohort report':'Native promotion'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for free-shipping promotions</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} is useful when the store defines the threshold, eligible products, customer state, and margin guardrails before sending. Recent purchasers and open service cases should usually be excluded.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Test free shipping against a non-offer message or holdout where practical, then review net margin, order value, returns, unsubscribes, and code leakage. A higher conversion rate is not enough if the offer destroys contribution.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports a controlled offer test; can use Shopify cart and order data.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; shipping cost and promotion volume materially affect economics.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official plans plus shipping, coupon, contacts, sends, and SMS costs.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Offer priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Detailed eligibility logic</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible event segmentation.</td></tr><tr><td>Simple offer sequence</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused campaign operations.</td></tr><tr><td>Native announcement</td><td>Shopify Email</td><td>Fast setup.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Continue with the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">discount-strategy guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
